item.description: My name is Jacob Vendl and I am a student at the University of Colorado Boulder, in the Aerospace Engineering department. My interests include aerospace engineering and its applications, astrodynamics, and soccer data analytics. I have worked as a primary researcher at the MIT Lincoln Laboratory, CU’s Center for Aerospace Structures, and L3Harris Applied Defense Solutions. My hobbies include skiing, paragliding, running, watching and playing soccer, and spending time with family and friends.
